    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-11-22T03:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-11-22T03:00:00-05:00" n="666"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d666">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.156/61: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China (<persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_JNT1"
                            type="from">Johnson</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-11-22T16:00:00+08:00"
                            >November 22, 1932—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received November 22—11:20 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1270. Your mail instruction No. 699, February 19 (no file number, Legation file
                    852 Shanghai foreshore regulations). A note has now been received from the
                    Ministry of Foreign Affairs referring to previous correspondence and requesting
                    that interested American[s] be instructed to comply with the revised foreshore
                    regulations promulgated by the municipality of Shanghai on July 31, 1931.</p>
                <pb facs="0705" n="607" xml:id="pg_607"/>
                <p>In view of the receipt of this further note, should Legation now take the action
                    directed in the Department’s instruction referred to above?</p>
                <closer>For the Minister:<lb/>
                    <signed>
                        <persName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Perkins</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
